d:desc.p:
Unless there is a BOM, the character encoding
    for the document must be specified in e.g. HTTP‐level,
    as:

To represent & as a data character, use
    named entity reference:
      &amp;

The < character as a data character must
    be escaped as:
    &lt;

dl.dd:
An XBL binding cannot be associated by 
      PI in HTML
      document.  Use binding property in CSS
      style sheet as:
        <style>
p {
  binding: url(binding.xbl);
}
</style>

d:desc.p:
To specify the character encoding used for serialization,
    if necessary, use XML declaration instead:
      <?xml version="1.0" encoding="encoding-name"?>

dd.p:
Values Expires, Pragma,
        and Cache-Control are not allowed;
        use real HTTP header fields for cache control.

d:item.d:message:
Conformance checking for script
  language $0 is not supported;
  it might or might not be conforming.

Conformance checking for style
  language $0 is not supported;
  it might or might not be conforming.
